# Markdown language

All `.md` file content in this project must be written in **English**.

This applies to:

- `README.md` and root-level docs
- Everything under `docs/`
- Roadmaps, checklists, ADRs, and any other Markdown files

When creating or updating Markdown:

- Use English for headings, body text, table cells, and checklist items
- Keep code blocks, file paths, and technical identifiers unchanged
- Do not mix Vietnamese or other languages into project documentation unless the user explicitly requests an exception for a specific file

Chat responses to the user may still use their preferred language; only persisted `.md` files follow this rule.
